    <worksheet name='Revelation Order vs Mushaf Order scatter plot'>
      <layout-options>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#141413' fontname='Anthropic Sans,system-ui,Segoe UI,Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'>This is a really interesting viz — it shows how the order surahs were revealed differs from their order in the mushaf (Quran book).</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>What this visualization reveals:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The Quran is NOT arranged chronologically</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> — if it were, all points would lie on a diagonal line from bottom-left to top-right. Instead, the scatter is widely dispersed.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Meccan surahs (blue) dominate the early revelations</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> (low Y values, bottom of chart) but are placed all across the mushaf (spread across X axis). The earlier revelations were mostly from Mecca.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Medinan surahs (orange) were revealed later</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> (higher Y values) but are placed EARLY in the mushaf (low X values, left side). Al-Baqara (surah 2) was the 87th revealed — almost last!</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The arrangement principle is roughly &quot;longest first&quot;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> rather than chronological — that&apos;s why the long Medinan surahs sit at the front of the mushaf despite being revealed later.</run>
            <run>
The plot of sum of Revelation Order for Mushaf Order.  
Color shows details about Revelation Place.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources>
            <datasource caption='quran_surahs' name='federated.0nyq5lu1vpdke31952giy10rt0ck' />
          </datasources>
          <datasource-dependencies datasource='federated.0nyq5lu1vpdke31952giy10rt0ck'>
            <column caption='Mushaf Order' datatype='integer' name='[mushaf_order]' role='measure' type='quantitative' />
